---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AppShell from '../../../components/AppShell.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Achilles Tendon - Fitness - Gabriele Angeletti"
  description="Comprehensive guide to achilles tendon care, strengthening exercises, and injury prevention strategies."
>
  <AppShell>
    <div class="p-4 lg:py-18">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="breadcrumbs text-sm mb-8">
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/fitness" class="text-primary hover:underline">Fitness</a></li>
            <li><a href="/fitness#training" class="text-primary hover:underline">Training</a></li>
            <li>Achilles Tendon</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Achilles Tendon</h1>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-base-content mb-2">Links</h3>
            <ul class="text-base-content/80 space-y-1">
                <li>• <a href="https://www.physio-pedia.com/Achilles_Tendon">Physio-pedia</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-12">
          <section class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h2 class="card-title text-2xl mb-6">Strengthening Exercises</h2>
              <div class="space-y-8">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-secondary pl-6">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Isometric Holds</h3>
                    <p class="text-base-content/80 mb-3">
                        Useful for early-stage rehabilitation. Good for for acute pain management, as it's been shown to reduce pain.<br>
                        Note: increase intensity by adding weight, not increasing reps or duration. It's been shown that 45 seconds of isometric hold is enough to send a stimulus to the tendon.
                    </p>
                    <div class="bg-base-200 p-4 rounded-lg">
                        <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Protocol:</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                            <li>• Hold single-leg calf raise for 45''</li>
                            <li>• 5 repetitions, 1 minute rest between</li>
                            <li>• Pain should be 3/10 or less</li>
                            <li>• If painless, increase intensity</li>
                            <li>• 3x per week</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6">
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Eccentric Calf Raises</h3>
                  <p class="text-base-content/80 mb-3">
                      Gold standard for Achilles tendinopathy rehabilitation. Emphasize the slow movement, 3'' to rise, 3'' to lower, to promote tendon remodeling. Hold something for balance (this is not a balance exercise).<br>
                      Note: if single-leg calf raises are too painful, consider raising with both legs and lowering with the affected leg only.
                  </p>
                  <div class="bg-base-200 p-4 rounded-lg">
                    <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Protocol:</h4>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                      <li>• Stand on edge of step with forefoot only</li>
                      <li>• Single-leg calf raise: 3'' to rise, 3'' to lower</li>
                      <li>• 3 sets of 15 reps</li>
                      <li>• Pain should be 4/10 or less</li>
                      <li>• Progress by adding weight</li>
                      <li>• 2x per week</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Stretching & Mobility -->
          <section class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h2 class="card-title text-2xl mb-6">Stretching & Mobility</h2>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div class="space-y-4">
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Static Stretches</h3>
                  <div class="space-y-3">
                    <div class="p-4 bg-base-200 rounded-lg">
                      <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Wall Push Stretch</h4>
                      <p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">
                        Hands against wall, step back affected leg. Keep heel down, lean forward.
                        Hold 30-60 seconds, 3 times.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-4 bg-base-200 rounded-lg">
                      <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Towel Stretch</h4>
                      <p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">
                        Sitting, loop towel around foot. Pull toes toward shin, hold 30 seconds.
                        Repeat 3 times.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Dynamic Mobility</h3>
                  <div class="space-y-3">
                    <div class="p-4 bg-base-200 rounded-lg">
                      <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Ankle Circles</h4>
                      <p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">
                        10 circles each direction. Focus on full range of motion.
                        Good warm-up exercise.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-4 bg-base-200 rounded-lg">
                      <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Calf Pumps</h4>
                      <p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">
                        Point and flex foot 20 times. Promotes blood flow and reduces stiffness.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 text-center">
          <a href="/fitness" class="btn btn-outline">
            ← Back to Fitness
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </AppShell>
</Layout>
